Create, read, update, and delete Frappe documents.

Examples:
  weg doc get User Administrator           # Get a document
  weg doc list User --limit 10             # List documents
  weg doc delete User test@test.com        # Delete document
  weg doc rename User old-name new-name    # Rename document
  weg doc export User Administrator        # Export to JSON
  weg doc import user.json                 # Import from JSON
  weg doc field get User Administrator email  # Get field value

Usage:
  weg doc [command]

Available Commands:
  delete      Delete a document
  export      Export a document to JSON
  field       Get or set document field values
  get         Get a document
  import      Import a document from JSON
  list        List documents
  rename      Rename a document

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for doc

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg doc [command] --help" for more information about a command.
